-- Nigeria Distributes $3.9 Billion to Tiers of Governments
-- B y   M a r a m   M a z e n
-- 2012-03-19T20:08:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/nigeria-distributes-3-9-billion-to-federal-state-governments.html
Nigeria  distributed 620.7 billion
naira ($3.9 billion) in revenue to federal, state and local
governments in February, Jonah Otunla, the country’s accountant-
general, said.  The figure is 1.1 percent higher than the previous month,
Otunla said in a statement handed to reporters today in Abuja,
the capital.  Nigeria,  Africa ’s top oil producer, received total revenue
of 766.8 billion naira in February compared with 666.3 billion
in the previous month, according to the statement.  Oil revenue rose to 632 billion naira in February from
523.9 billion naira in the previous month, the statement said.
Non-oil revenue fell to 74.8 billion naira in February from 72.5
billion in the previous month, it said. The total revenue
available for distribution also includes value-added tax and
refunds by the state-owned Nigerian National Petroleum Corp.,
according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
